race.comment: CAPITAL DESIGN (6) returns from a short break. Was unlucky not to get off the mark on debut at Cowra in September when beaten a head. Looks to have come on a treat since, benefiting from a dominant trial win. Clearly looks the one to beat. SCUSIES (12) raced on the speed last time but couldn't finish off at Ballarat. Was much better the start prior when beaten less than a length at Echuca. McDougall's booking suggests she's figured it out and can fire this time. ALL ABOUT LIZZIE (11) is an All Too Hard filly on debut for the Smith yard. Has jumped out well in readiness and is expected to make her presence felt. DER BLAUE REITER (1) returns and it's worth noting he went well fresh last campaign when narrowly missing in Canberra. Keeping safe.
